--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot; RetroCom&quot; &lt;vfp19968@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; A common, basic VHS VCR can be used as a low noise analog recorder. I 
supplied a crystal microphone and audio pre-amplifier and fed this into 
the &#39;audio in&#39; on the VCR. Playback can be monitored on a TV set or the 
audio out can be fed to a computer. I post processed in ClearVoice to 
remove a slight 60hz hum and reduce the high frequencies. Background 
sound was provided by a high speed manual sweep tune of an FM broadcast 
radio. Here&#39;s a couple of the best so far.
